<FONT FACE="Arial, Verdana, Helvetica" size="-1">

 

	
	
	
	
	
	

	
	

	
	
	
	
	
	
	<table border="0" width="100%" bgcolor="000000" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
      <tr>
        <td width="100%">
          <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0">
            <tr>
              <td width="100%" bgcolor="bfbf80" background="">
                <font face="arial">
				<center>
				<strong><font color="4a0000">Abuse of the Play Nice Policy</strong></font><br>
				</center>
              </td>
            </tr>
			<tr>
              <td width="100%" bgcolor="CDCD9C" background="">
              <p align="center"><font face="arial" size="2">News Contributed By:
              <a href="mailto:dantes@eqrealms.com"><font color="ca0000"><b>Dantes</a></b></font><br>
              </font><font face="arial" size="1">Monday, June 5, 2000</font></td>
            </tr>
			<tr>
              <td width="100%" bgcolor="CDCD9C">
                &nbsp;
                <div align="center">
                  <center>
                  <table border="0" width="98%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%"><font face="arial" size="2">Some rants I've read on various EQ forums have mentioned the Play Nice Policy actually causing more problems and doing more harm than good.  An example would be a rude person who comes to a camped spawn which has been held by the same group for many hours and demands to be able to share a rare spawn.  An example would be the Lord in Lower Guk.  The way people run groups in most popular dungeons is to hold lists for those groups and allow anyone who wants on the list to be put on it, when an opening comes up they are notified and they can join the group.  The Play Nice Policies totally screw that up, they basically make it so that any other group of folks can show up and demand to cut the spawn in half.  Considering we're talking about something like the Lord, how often does the Lord actually spawn?  Not that often. So what if you have 2 people in your group who need SMRs, and another group comes along and demands to share that means the second time this really rare spawn comes up they get to kill it even though your group has been there longer and has waited longer and may have cleared the spawn.  How is that fair and nice?  The Play Nice Policy allows rude, pushy, and greedy people to abuse GMs to get what they want.</font>
                        <p>&nbsp;
					  </td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  </center>
                </div>
              </td>
            </tr>
